11/03/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- US President Barack Obama will visit Turkey on April 6th and 7th to attend an annual forum of the UN-led Alliance of Civilisations in Istanbul, media quoted Spanish diplomatic sources as saying on Tuesday (March 10th). 
The Alliance initiative's co-chairmen are Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan and his Spanish counterpart, Jose Luis Rodriguez Zapatero.
Also Tuesday, Turkish President Abdullah Gul said Obama's planned visit was very important for both Ankara and Washington, as it would present an opportunity to boost bilateral relations, which he described as "one of the main pillars of Turkish foreign policy". 
(EFE, Hurriyet, ANSA, ANKA - 10/03/09)
